The 25-year-old suspect, who had recently been released from prison, was taken into custody following the toddler's death on Sunday. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town police say a Khayelitsha father has been arrested for the rape and murder of his two-year-old daughter.The 25-year-old suspect, who had recently been released from prison, was taken into custody following the toddler's death on Sunday morning. Cape Town police say the two-year-old's father had requested to spend time with his daughter after having been recently released from prison. On Sunday morning, he alerted the child's grandmother that the child was not breathing. The woman rushed the child to the Khayelitsha Day Hospital where doctors certified her dead. Lingelethu Police officials arrested the 25-year old father shortly afterwards.Rape and murder cases are being investigated and the suspect is expected to appear in court this week.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)